funk /fʌŋk/

(funks) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Funk is a style of dance music based on jazz and blues, with a strong, repeated bass part. 疯克乐; 融合了爵士乐和蓝调乐的舞蹈音乐，低音部分多重复，力度强 

例： ...a mixture of experimental jazz, soul and funk. ...实验性爵士乐、灵魂乐和疯克乐的混合。 

2. N-COUNT A funk is a state of mind in which you feel sad or depressed. 忧愁 [usu sing] 

例： I was at loose ends and in a funk. 我无所事事，心情愁苦。 

例： She's really helped me out of the funk I was in. 她真的给我了很大帮助，帮我从消沉的情绪中走出。 

3. N a strong foul odour 强烈的臭气 [美国英语] [slang] 

4. V to flinch from (responsibility) through fear (因恐慌而对责任)逃避

